Dear Martin

Your model seems to be one where cholesterol is measured at the study 
level not the individual level so it is predicting that in a study where 
the average drop in cholesterol was zero the average drop in 
atherosclerosis would be 4mm. It does not tell you what happens to an 
individual patient. One would need a lot more information about what was 
going on in the studies to tell whether that is plausible and whether it 
has implication at the individual level.

Michael

